metadata.title: DPM Dar, UAE counterpart discuss regional, global issues

content.article_body: ISLAMABAD, April 21 (APP): Deputy Prime Minister/Foreign Minister Senator Mohammad Ishaq Dar and Deputy Prime Minister/Foreign Minister of the United Arab Emirates (UAE) Sheikh Abdullah bin Zayed Al Nahyan on Monday held cordial and in-depth discussions. "Besides the focus on further cementing excellent bilateral relations, regional and global issues of mutual interest and concern discussed in a candid ambiance," Foreign Office Spokesperson said in a press release.
